   Kiss A Pig
   Bankers Life Fieldhouse

      Kiss a Pig
      Bankers Life FieldHouse

      Thank you to ALL of the 2014 Kiss a Pig Candidates and Donors! Because
      of YOU, we raised more than 123,000 to help Stop Diabetes in Indiana!
      Hogs and Kisses to the 2014 Kiss a Pig Winners!

      Kiss a Pig Winners-2014

      Linda DiMeglio, MD- (IU/Riley Hospital) - Health Organization Category

      kiss a pig winner-2014

      Edward Bonach,CEO (CNO Financial Group) - Financial/Insurance Category

      kiss a pig winner-2014

      Mike Arnoult (Walgreens) - Large Corporation Category


      Kiss A Pig and help STOP DIABETES!

      Pucker up and join us for the 2015 Kiss a Pig competition and another
      squealing good time! For more information or to become a candidate
      email Judi Williams, Manager, or call 317-352-9226

      The purpose of Kiss a Pig is
      threefold:
                 KAP Cropped
        * To increase public awareness about diabetes and the American
          Diabetes Association
        * To encourage prompt diagnosis and proper treatment of diabetes
        * To raise funds to support the American Diabetes
          Association's research, education services and advocacy programs

      Candidates will compete and raise funds for the American Diabetes
      Association. The candidate who brings home the most bacon will pucker
      up and kiss a real, live piglet at center court during half time!

      Why a pig?  It's our way of expressing gratitude to the pig for its
      life-saving role as one of the first sources of insulin.  Since 1921,
      insulin has played a major role in the treatment of diabetes for
      millions of people who suffer from this disease.

      WE ARE RECRUITING CANDIDATES AND WE WANT YOU TO KISS A PIG!

      To learn more about Kiss A Pig or to become a 2015 candidate email
      [27]Judi Williams, Manager, 317-352-9226, ext. 6727.


      Meet Our 2014 Kiss A Pig Candidates and Winners!


